  "texts": [
    "QuestEval (Scialom et al., 2021) and MQAG (Manakul et al., 2023a) are QA-based approaches for assessing consistency in summarization tasks.",
    "QuestEval uses extracted answer spans while MQAG represents information using multiplechoice questions.",
    "Both methods are reference-free.",
    "Longformer-SFT: For podcast summarization, we follow Manakul and Gales (2022) in using a Supervised Fine-Tuned longformer (Beltagy et al., 2020) as a baseline.",
    "The input is the document and the summary, and human judgement is used as the supervised target label at training, and the performance is reported using 5-fold cross-validation."
